text: Mont Poupet is a mountain in the Jura Mountains, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, eastern France. With an elevation of , it is located in the commune of Saint- Thiébaud. From up there you can look down over the whole valley of Salins-les- Bains. The mountain is mostly composed of limestone. Category:Mountains of Bourgogne-Franche-Comté
title: Mont Poupet
